					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure class="mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Xun_Zi.PNG" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/75/Xun_Zi.PNG/250px-Xun_Zi.PNG" decoding="async" width="250" height="135" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/75/Xun_Zi.PNG/500px-Xun_Zi.PNG 1.5x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="323" /></a><figcaption>Learning proceeds until <a href="/wiki/Death" title="Death">death</a> and only then does it stop... Its <a href="/wiki/Purpose" title="Purpose">purpose</a> cannot be given up for even a <a href="/wiki/Moment" title="Moment">moment</a>.  To pursue it is to be <a href="/wiki/Human" title="Human">human</a>, to give it up to be a <a href="/wiki/Beast" class="mw-redirect" title="Beast">beast</a>. ~ <a href="/wiki/Xun_Zi" class="mw-redirect" title="Xun Zi">Xun Zi</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:William_H._Crogman_(cropped).jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/William_H._Crogman_%28cropped%29.jpg/250px-William_H._Crogman_%28cropped%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="368" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/William_H._Crogman_%28cropped%29.jpg/375px-William_H._Crogman_%28cropped%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e5/William_H._Crogman_%28cropped%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="471" data-file-height="693" /></a><figcaption>He, therefore, who fixes a limit of any kind to his intellectual attainments dwarfs himself, and cramps the growth of that mind given to us by the Creator, and capable of indefinite expansion. ~ <a href="/wiki/William_H._Crogman" title="William H. Crogman">William H. Crogman</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg/250px-Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="302" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg/375px-Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8d/Muntzer_Muhlhausen02.jpg 2x" data-file-width="441" data-file-height="532" /></a><figcaption>You, the common man, must become learned yourself, so that you will be misled no longer. ~ <a href="/wiki/Thomas_M%C3%BCntzer" title="Thomas Müntzer">Thomas Müntzer</a></figcaption></figure>
<p><b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning" class="extiw" title="w:Learning">Learning</a></b> is the acquisition and development of <a href="/wiki/Memory" title="Memory">memories</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/behaviors" class="extiw" title="w:behaviors">behaviors</a>, including <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/skill" class="extiw" title="w:skill">skills</a>, <a href="/wiki/Knowledge" title="Knowledge">knowledge</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/understanding" class="extiw" title="w:understanding">understanding</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Value_(personal_and_cultural)" class="extiw" title="w:Value (personal and cultural)">values</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Wisdom" title="Wisdom">wisdom</a>.  It is the goal of <a href="/wiki/Education" title="Education">education</a>, and the product of <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a>.
</p>
<div role="navigation" style="margin-left: 2em;">
